    "A Valid Path" is the fourth solo album by English rock musician Alan Parsons. The record was released on 24 August 2004 via Artemis label.

    The gap between this and his previous album, The Time Machine, was the third greatest period between two consecutive albums, after the time between the split of The Alan Parsons Project and Parsons' first solo work (not counting Freudiana) and the time between this album and The Secret. In addition to contributors such as David Gilmour, another noteworthy musical credit on the album is Parsons' son Jeremy; his debut appearance on his father's albums.

    A Valid Path was released on Audio CD and DualDisc, with the DualDisc containing the album recorded in 5.1 Surround in both DTS and Dolby Digital formats. Other features of the DualDisc include a track commentary by the artist and interviews with Alan Parsons and the main collaborators on the release including David Gilmour and the Crystal Method.

    Release Info
    This release is ripped from the DualDisc release of A Valid Path.
    I've converted the DTS tracks to Dolby Digital Plus (E-AC-3, Apple compliant).

    Tracklist
    01. Return to Tunguska (featuring Shpongle & David Gilmour) 08:48
    02. More Lost Without You (featuring P.J. Olsson) 03:20
    03. Mammagamma 04 (featuring Jeremy Parsons) 05:06
    04. We Play the Game (featuring the Crystal Method) 05:33
    05. Tijuaniac (featuring Nortec Collective) 05:21
    06. L'Arc En Ciel (dedicated to Anson Grossfeld 1957-2004, featuring berzone) 05:26
    07. A Recurring Dream Within a Dream (featuring Jeremy Parsons, narration by Orson Welles) 04:06
    08. You Can Run (featuring David Pack) 03:51
    09. Chomolungma (featuring Jeremy Parsons and P.J. Olsson, narration by John Cleese and a dog) 06:35
    10. The Time Machine (hidden bonustrack, version without narration) 03:37

    Note to the peeps @ RuTracker: Give credit if you post the work of someone else!

    Genre: Electronic, Rock
    Style: Synth-pop, Prog Rock
    Year: 2023 (original release: 1988)

    "The Instrumental Works" is a 1988 compilation album by The Alan Parsons Project, featuring many of the band's instrumental tracks. The 24- bit version of the release is released on Qobuz on December 1, 2023. The 24-bit version has 7 tracks more than the original (17 instead of 10). I've added the 18th track as an extra bonus (Sirius 2017 Disco Demolition Remix - 16-bit).

    Tracklist
    01. Sirius 01:47
    02. Mammagamma 03:35
    03. Voyager 02:14
    04. I Robot 06:02
    05. The Gold Bug 04:36
    06. Chinese Whispers 01:04
    07. Lucifer 05:11
    08. Genesis Ch.1. V.32 03:19
    09. Hyper-Gamma-Spaces 04:20
    10. The Ace of Swords 02:58

    14. Paseo de Gracia 03:52
    15. Where's the Walrus? 07:34
    16. Urbania 05:03
    17. Pipeline 03:57
    Bonustrack (16-bit)
    18. Sirius 2017 (Disco Demolition Remix) 03:45
